cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.SI 

The paper presents a novel theoretical kernel-based framework for node classification on graphs, which is related to representation learning. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The proposed framework also involves feature aggregation and similarity metrics, which are commonly used in Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) tasks. Finally, the paper evaluates the approach on standard benchmarks, which is a common practice in the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category.
